<br>
But anyhow, my Water pet with Burnout 4 and Muzzle does seem to get 70dps generall on normal PoP mobs, as long as its gett backstabs in.  Drops to around 50dps if its not getting backstabs.  So basically the pet's base DPS is 50 plus 20 for backstabbing.<br>
<br>
This doesn't count its spell casting of course.<br>
<br>
Quite obviously the pet is doing AMAZING damage for something that we barely have to pay attention to.<br>
<br>
Grouping with a 65th Paladin the other day, who was using Tunare Sword, he was only getting about 73dps (didnt have max haste though) so our pets are really putting out good damage.<br>
<br>
However thats just against normal PoP mobs.<br>
<br>
Against SLIGHTLY more uber mobs his DPS goes WAY down.<br>
<br>
Was doing the Giant Lords in PoS, and the pet's damage drops down to about 25dps.  Now thats without backstabs as the mobs were moving around  a lot.  but even if you add say 10dps for backstabs (we'll take 10 as his normal dps went down by half from 50 to 25, so we'll say his backstab dps would drop by the same amount from 20 to 10).<br>
<br>
Now I've seen all these posts saying that pets can do 80dps on uber mobs?  I'd like to see some parses of that.  If I can stop being lazy later I'll even post a couple parses myself.<br>
<br>
And as to using pets on any mob that has a good AE, I feel there isnt really a point.  If you can summon the pet b4 the fight and send it in at the beginning, and let it last as long as it can, thats fine.  Certainly no point in healing it or resumoning a new one, as it would be more mana efficient, and more time efficient, to just nuke more.<br>
<br>
I don't have the best resists, but on fights where a boss has an AE I get mine up to the 200-250 range usually, and my pet is still getting eaten really quickly.  For instance Grummas, pet dies REAL fast.   Thats partly because Grummas's AE has a -1000 resists check on it I guess.  But my point basically is that on AE mobs that I've tested the pet on, its really not worthwhile wasting time with a pet.  And from the parses of the Giants in PoS since they are only doing 25dps, its not like we are gaining HUGE damage from them.  Jsut a nice addition to our normal Nuking. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.blackcompany.cc/member_pics/329.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
